An employee who interacts with the public has tested positive for the coronavirus, BART officials said. 

The person last worked last Sunday, wore a mask and gloves and practiced social distancing while spending time in stations and on trains.

text:
The Bay Area is rolling forward with reopening the economy even as coronavirus case counts are comparable to or much higher than the earliest days of the outbreak.

Story by @ErinAllday: https://t.co/xYxVpaVD83 https://t.co/bIxvDtKBgC

name: sfchronicle
text:
Santa Cruz and Monterey counties announced they will open to outside leisure travelers on Friday. 

Restrictions will be lifted on: 

• Hotels
• Wineries
• Restaurants
• Bars
• Vacation rentals
• Museums
• Zoos
• Gyms
• Pools
• Campgrounds

https://t.co/qAs6pWNbXP
